- "More of a particular style and size" refers to the total quantity of items purchased for a specific style and size chart ID;
- "Currently available in the inventory" refers to the total quantity of items in stock for the same style and size chart ID;
- The query filters out cases where the total quantity purchased does not exceed the inventory quantity.

- "graceful ladies" refers to female customers;
- "fit the European standard of 35 inches (88 cm) hips" refers to the size chart entry where the hip measurement is 35 inches (88 cm) in the European standard;
- "unique identifiers in the size chart" refers to the size chart IDs.

- "Top three most abundant" refers to the styles with the highest total quantity in the inventory;
- "High confidence in their size recommendations" means the confidence score is greater than 0.9;
- "Recommended measurements" include bust, waist, and hips.

- "recommended measurements" refer to the size chart entries recommended to customers based on their latest body measurements;
- "actual measurements" refer to the size chart entries of the garments customers have most recently purchased;
- The differences in measurements (bust, waist, and absolute bust) help assess the accuracy of size recommendations.

- "Loyal patrons" refers to customers who have made multiple purchases;
- "Tailored fit" refers to the recommendations of sizes that match their measurements;
- "Favored styles" refers to the styles they frequently purchase;
- "Purchase history" includes the number of purchases and the total amount spent.

- Size recommendations are based on the most recent algorithm version;
- The query ensures that at least one measurement (bust, waist, hips, shoulder, sleeve_length, inseam) from the customer's body matches the recommended or purchased size;
- The countries considered are France (FR), the UK (UK), and Europe (EUR).

sql:
SELECT AVG(cm.bust) AS average_bust
FROM customer_measurements cm
INNER JOIN size_recommendations sr ON cm.customer_id = sr.customer_id;

SELECT country_code, COUNT(size_standard_id) AS number_of_size_standards
FROM size_standards
GROUP BY country_code;

